            "contentString": "{patientName} has a significant 37 pack-year smoking history (1 PPD from ages 21–58) and quit smoking 13 years ago. She has a background of well-controlled hypertension managed with lifestyle measures and mild chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD, GOLD Stage I) diagnosed incidentally on spirometry five years ago, for which she uses an as-needed bronchodilator. She was hospitalized once at age 64 for community-acquired pneumonia, requiring a four-day inpatient admission. She has no prior history of malignancy and no prior thoracic surgery. She underwent a right lower lobe CT-guided percutaneous needle biopsy four months ago confirming non-small cell lung adenocarcinoma, followed by a bronchoscopy with biopsy for additional tissue characterization. PET-CT staging revealed the primary right lower lobe mass with mediastinal lymph node involvement but no distant metastases (Stage IIIA). She has no known cardiac arrhythmias or diabetes. Her functional status at baseline was ECOG Performance Status 1. She reports a penicillin allergy (rash) from childhood. Her current oncology regimen consists of Carboplatin + Pemetrexed chemotherapy combined with Pembrolizumab immunotherapy, with supportive antiemetics and corticosteroids. She is closely monitored with interval imaging and pulmonary function assessments."
